headline: Robinhood Ventures Fund I Opens Private Markets As Stock Faces Volatility
summary: Robinhood Markets (NasdaqGS:HOOD) is launching Robinhood Ventures Fund I, a publicly traded vehicle giving retail investors access to private companies such as SpaceX, Databricks, and Stripe. The fund IPO, led by Goldman Sachs, is set up with no minimum investment threshold, opening participation to non accredited investors. This structure introduces a new way for individual investors to gain exposure to private markets that were previously limited to institutions and accredited...
